nib.text:
Over 3,400 customers lost power in Whittier after a car thief collided with an electric pole Monday afternoon.

A 911 caller reported a collision with injuries soon after 3 p.m. near E. 26th Street & Nicollet Avenue S.

Citizen user video on the scene showed a downed power line.

First responders reported a man stole a vehicle and collided with the pole, then fled on foot.

Firefighters blocked traffic at Blaisdell Avenue.

Xcel Energy confirmed one outage in the area began shortly after 3 p.m. affecting 2,144 customers. It was forecast to be resolved around 5 p.m.

Xcel Energy confirmed another outage nearby began around 3:30 p.m. and affected at leat 1,346 customers. See the outage map [here](https://www.outagemap-xcelenergy.com/outagemap/). The outage was forecast to be repaired  by 6:41 p.m.

-MvqJU2Qz_pO_3y-58oU.text: Police have received an unconfirmed report of a man armed with a knife.

-MvqKjGE139bPJCuUgmD.text: Police have requested medics to respond to the scene.

-MvqLk2oVALKT4VM9Plc.text: Police on the scene confirmed a man armed with a butcher knife. They have also reported that no one has been injured.

-MvqNEMZqSSBc2ulDhWi.text: Police have advised that the suspect armed with a knife said to be not complying.

-MvqOOBMhN9DZ2S3yHxo.text: Police report that the suspect has exited the residence and is on the porch. The suspect has not reportedly harmed anyone. All the other residents have secured themselves in a nearby residence.

-MvqOoV4YsVwWgT-jj73.text: Officers have requested additional units to assist as they attempt to gain the suspect's compliance.

-Mvqn2DTEaM4G4WZgLuC.text: Police advise that the man is now armed with a machete and a knife.

-MvqnHdNldDwhvC_Txam.text: Police have set a perimeter and have been attempting to make contact with the suspect.

-MvqnSu9k44AIILwCrkb.text: The suspect has reportedly been moving from the front porch through the house to the back porch.

-MvqnaWl0fOvSe0dQHk9.text: Police are attempting to call the suspect's phone to make contact.

-MvqncTOucnFDXZPysRk.text: Police have made contact with the suspect.

-MvqneUNRL-INu-v_WDr.text: EMS has staged in the area.

-MvqnoCb2OcnglAIbC5G.text: According to the victim, the suspect attempted to break into her residence and threatened her.

-Mvqott2bG8GohzELvQg.text: SWAT has arrived at the scene. Police are broadening their perimeter and are blocking all pedestrian and vehicular traffic.

-MvqprH5mkvyRVf3uObW.text: Police are blocking traffic at N Park St and Winnipeg Ave W, N Park St and Manitoba Ave, N Park St and W Wayzata St, and Manitoba Ave W and Rice St.

-MvqpxwE8Lr3J9NpJyXy.text: An armored vehicle has arrived at the scene.

-MvqrosWDMU1HsVwa1rH.text: Police report that the suspect has been playing a game of phone-tag where officers will make contact with him for awhile and he will hang up before answering again.

-MvqrxuKeyvxJ-lg6K8Q.text: The suspect may reportedly leave his residence, though this is unconfirmed.

-MvrA-z_xjLxbyCvza2t.text: Citizen user Minnesota_News' video shows the perimeter set around the barricaded suspect.

-MvrAl0iHqnQhrihNt2t.text: A Lenco BearCat, which is a wheeled armored-personnel carrier designed for military and law enforcement use, has been deployed along with SWAT members.

-MvrRWrsg9jyZbUe1_kC.text: Police have re-established phone contact with the suspect.

-MvrSqJzlp_gsKRCY28e.text: Police have deployed pepper balls, which are projectiles containing a powdered chemical that irritates the eyes and nose, into the residence.

-MvrSyMgu0sQm9xXhsgf.text: Police are deploying a robot to assist with the scene.

-MvrTA4f68n_QtaqvWyw.text: Police have deployed the robot which attempted to block the suspect into a bathroom. The suspect allegedly left the bathroom and walked past the robot into the kitchen.

-MvrTKj6ivkQOtISPlnN.text: Police are issuing verbal commands to the suspect.

-MvrTXYcI_IYwqlkGBR4.text: According to officers, the suspect is lighting a fire in the kitchen. Multiple irritants have been fired into the residence to deter him, but they are reportedly not having any effect.

-MvrU-_1hqTJURG0iEqQ.text: Police are continuing to deploy the robot and other methods to pacify the suspect. According to an officer, the suspect is attempting to wash his face or cover his eyes with a rag.

-MvrUEUZT9F53Ab8J8ZC.text: The suspect reportedly moved to the living room and then back into the bathroom. Units are attempting to contain him inside the bathroom.

-MvrUtXNKDADV4ENNsmi.text: Police have placed the suspect in custody. EMS has been requested to assess the suspect for any potential injuries.

-MvrV2fcq0DimEjD-MN9.text: Firefighters are en route to assess the building for any potential fires.

-MvrVPhNOp6FebQDGiGS.text: Police report that the residence needs to be ventilated. Officers report that nothing appears to be on fire, but the suspect did turn on a gas burner.
